!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

curl /kɜːl/

(curling,curled,curls) 

1. N-COUNT If you have curls , your hair is in the form of tight curves and spirals. 卷发 

例： ...the little girl with blonde curls. …长着金黄色卷发的小女孩。 

2. N-COUNT A curl of something is a piece or quantity of it that is curved or spiral in shape. 卷曲状或螺旋状 

例： A thin curl of smoke rose from a rusty stove. 一缕薄薄的青烟从生锈的炉子里冉冉升起。 

3. N-UNCOUNT If your hair has curl , it is full of curls. 卷曲 

例： Dry curly hair naturally for maximum curl and shine. 让卷发自然地风干以最大限度地增加头发的卷曲和光泽。 

4. V-T/V-I If your hair curls or if you curl it, it is full of curls. 卷曲; 使卷曲 

例： She has hair that refuses to curl. 她的头发怎么也不卷。 

例： Maria had curled her hair for the event. 玛丽亚为这次活动卷了头发。 

5. V-T/V-I If your toes, fingers, or other parts of your body curl , or if you curl them, they form a curved or round shape. 弯曲; 使弯曲 

例： His fingers curled gently around her wrist. 他的手指轻握住她的手腕。 

例： Raise one foot, curl the toes and point the foot downwards. 抬起一只脚，将脚趾弯曲，将脚向下指。 

6. V-T/V-I If something curls somewhere, or if you curl it there, it moves there in a spiral or curve. 缭绕; 使缠绕 

例： Smoke was curling up the chimney. 烟顺着烟囱缭绕升起。 

7. V-I If a person or animal curls into a ball, they move into a position in which their body makes a rounded shape. 蜷作一团 

例： He wanted to curl into a tiny ball. 他想把自己蜷成一个小团。 

8. PHRASAL VERB Curl up means the same as . 蜷作一团 

例： In colder weather, your cat will curl up into a tight, heat-conserving ball. 在更冷的天气里，你的猫会蜷缩成紧紧的一团来保暖。 

例： She curled up next to him. 她蜷卧在他身边。 

9. V-I When a leaf, a piece of paper, or another flat object curls , its edges bend toward the centre. 卷边 

例： The rose leaves have curled because of an attack by grubs. 玫瑰的叶子因虫子的侵袭打了卷。 

10. PHRASAL VERB Curl up means the same as . 卷起 

例： The corners of the rug were curling up. 地毯的各角卷起来了。

